    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://gonzalezgarcia.github.io/authors/admin/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://gonzalezgarcia.github.io/authors/admin/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;My research interests concern the neurocognitive mechanisms underlying perception, attention and control processes. Specifically, I am interested in how the brain takes advantage of available (internal or external) information to guide cognition. I mostly follow a multivariate approach to combine neuroimaging data modalities with the ultimate goal of resolving in time and space how the brain drives flexible behavior.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At the moment, I am a &lt;b&gt;Marie Skłodowska-Curie&lt;/b&gt; postdoc fellow in Prof. &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://users.ugent.be/~mbrass/Web-Site/Dr._Marcel_Brass.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Marcel Brass&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt; lab at &lt;b&gt;Ghent University&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I received my PhD from the &lt;b&gt;University of Granada&lt;/b&gt;, where I worked with &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ugr.es/~mruz/esp/Inicio.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;María Ruz&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt;. As a grad student, I also spent some time as a Fulbright scholar at &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://med.nyu.edu/helab/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Biyu He&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&#39;s lab at &lt;b&gt;NIH and NYU&lt;b/&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can contact me at &lt;code&gt;cgonzalgarcia (at) gmail (dot) com&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
